Liverpool winger and Pharaohs skipper Mohamed Salah promised Egyptian fans that the team will fight in the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) in Cameroon to bring home an eighth African cup as he joined the national team training camp. “The road is not easy but we will fight to return home with the cup, support us,” Salah vowed in a post on his official Twitter account. Salah and Aston Villa’s Mahmoud Trezeguet were the last foreign-based players to join the Pharaohs training camp in Cairo in preparation for the Nations Cup, which will take place in Cameroon from 9 January to 6 February. The seven-time African champions, who are set to travel to Cameroon tomorrow , will play in Group D along with Nigeria, Sudan, and Guinea Bissau.   Akpeyi, Noble fancy Eagles chances     BetKing to fly five fans to watch AFCON finals     Covid chaos stop Senegal flight to Cameroon   The Pharaohs will start their campaign in the cup against the Nigerian Super Eagles on 11 January. - Advertisement - Meanwhile, Salah has been listed along with six more Premier League stars as L’Equipe reveal their best XI of 2021. The Egyptian missed out on FIFA’s World XI of 2021, but his sensational year has been recognised by L’Equipe, and he occupies the right flank in front of Liverpool team-mate Trent Alexander-Arnold. But L’Equipe has omitted Lionel Messi from their team of the year, while Manchester United superstar Cristiano Ronaldo has missed out too. Barring the glaring omissions of Messi and Ronaldo, PSG stars Neymar and Kylian Mbappe also do not feature in the team, nor does Borussia Dortmund marksman Erling Haaland.